THE EFFECTIVE FIELD THEORY OF MOTION–TIMESPACE
From the Microscopic ψ-Field to Emergent General Relativity and Cosmology

Martin Ollett (2025)


----------------------------------------------------------------------
Abstract
----------------------------------------------------------------------
We construct the full Effective Field Theory (EFT) of Motion–TimeSpace (MTS),
linking:
  (1) the microscopic Planck-scale motion field ψ(x),
  (2) the emergent macroscopic metric g_{μν},
  (3) the MTS-extended Einstein equations governing cosmology.

The microscopic nonlinear ψ-action:

      A_MTS[ψ] = ∫ [ (1/2c²)(∂_tψ)² − (1/2)(∇ψ)²
                     − (γ/2) ψ ∂_tψ − (λ/n)|ψ|^n ] d⁴x

produces the fundamental MTS equation:

      ∂²_tψ − c²∇²ψ + γ ∂_tψ + λ |ψ|^{n−1} = 0,

with n = 4/3 fixed by dimensional stability.

Coarse-graining the ψ-covariance defines the emergent metric:

      g_{μν} = η_{μν} + ⟨ ∂_μψ ∂_νψ ⟩_smooth.

Substituting this into the coarse-grained effective action yields the
MTS–Einstein functional:

      A[g] = ∫ [ (1/2κ) R − L_{Λκ} + L_matter ] √(-g) d⁴x,

with L_{Λκ} = (2/κ) Γ_G.

Variation gives the extended Einstein equation:

      G_{μν} + Γ_G g_{μν} = κ T_{μν}.

Γ_G is the Global Curvature Gradient measured in MBT-5 cosmology, unifying
dark matter and dark energy as curvature-exchange effects. This paper
establishes the complete EFT link: microscopic ψ → emergent GR →
cosmological dynamics.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Introduction
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Standard physics splits between:
  • General Relativity (classical geometry),
  • Quantum Mechanics (microscopic wavefunctions),
  • ΛCDM (phenomenological cosmology).

Motion–TimeSpace (MTS) replaces this with:
  • ψ(x) as a fundamental curvature–motion field,
  • geometry emerging from ψ-covariance,
  • GR as the infrared limit of ψ dynamics,
  • Γ_G as curvature-exchange encoded energy,
  • Planck-scale nonlinearity generating particle and soliton structure.

This paper connects all three scales via EFT.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
2. The Microscopic Motion Field ψ
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The fundamental field is:

      ψ : ℝ⁴ → ℝ.

Its gradients encode curvature–motion exchange:

      ∂_μ ψ: microscopic curvature flux
      ∂_μψ ∂_νψ: covariance of curvature exchange

Classical geometry emerges from statistical smoothing of ψ-gradients.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Emergent Metric Tensor
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Define:

      g_{μν}(x)
        = η_{μν}
          + ⟨ ∂_μψ(x) ∂_νψ(x) ⟩_smooth.

The averaging removes Planck-scale oscillations but preserves curvature.

Properties:
  • symmetric,
  • Lorentzian,
  • dynamic,
  • derived entirely from ψ.

This is the MTS mechanism for emergent spacetime.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
4. The Global Curvature Gradient Γ_G
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Cosmological analysis yields:

      Γ_G(z)
        = (α₀ + α₁ log(1+z)) log(1+z) + β z.

This single scalar:
  • reproduces Λ when constant,
  • unifies the dark sector when dynamical,
  • resolves the Hubble tension,
  • arises from the coarse-grained ψ energy–exchange history.

Γ_G therefore enters the action as a covariant scalar potential.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
5. The Microscopic MTS Action
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Planck-scale Lagrangian generating the fundamental ψ dynamics is:

      L_MTS
        = (1/2c²)(∂_tψ)²
          − (1/2)(∇ψ)²
          − (γ/2) ψ ∂_tψ
          − (λ/n)|ψ|^n,

with n = 4/3.

Thus:

      A_MTS[ψ] = ∫ L_MTS d⁴x.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Variation: The Fundamental MTS Field Equation
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Variation yields:

      ∂²_tψ − c²∇²ψ + γ ∂_tψ + λ |ψ|^{n−1} = 0.

n = 4/3 follows from dimensional stability of the energy functional:

      E ∼ ∫ (|∇ψ|² + |ψ|^n) d³x.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Determination of γ and λ
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The damping constant:

      γ = Φ_G √(c⁵/(Għ)).

The nonlinear coupling:

      λ = Φ_G³ (c³/G) γ.

These give the correct characteristic scale:

      L ≈ 1.6 × 10⁻³⁵ m.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
8. Effective Field Theory: ψ → g_{μν}
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The effective action is the coarse-grained functional integral:

      A_eff[g] = ⟨ A_MTS[ψ] ⟩_smooth.

Quadratic ψ-terms induce the Einstein–Hilbert term:

      ⟨ ∂_μψ ∂_νψ ⟩ → g_{μν} − η_{μν}  ⇒  R.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
9. The Macroscopic MTS–Einstein Action
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The emergent action is:

      A[g]
        = ∫ [ (1/2κ)R
               − L_{Λκ}
               + L_matter ] √(-g) d⁴x,

with:

      L_{Λκ} = (2/κ) Γ_G.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
10. Variation: The Extended Einstein Equation
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Variation gives:

      G_{μν} + Γ_G g_{μν} = κ T_{μν},

κ = 8πG/c⁴.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
11. Interpretation
----------------------------------------------------------------------
11.1 GR is the IR limit  
  Γ_G → 0   → GR  
  Γ_G → Λ   → ΛCDM  

11.2 Singularities removed  
  Γ_G → 1  ⇒  dτ/dt → 0  
Evolution halts before divergence.

11.3 Dark sector unified  
  ρ_phantom = (3/8πG) Γ_G  
matches dark matter & dark energy.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
12. Quantum Interpretation
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Microscopic ψ dynamics imply:

  • superposition = linear ψ,
  • collapse = nonlinear ψ + damping,
  • Born rule = |ψ|² energy density,
  • decoherence = environmental ψ coupling,
  • macroscopic classicality = γ scaling ∝ system size.


----------------------------------------------------------------------
13. Conclusion
----------------------------------------------------------------------
This work presents the complete Effective Field Theory of Motion–TimeSpace:

  1. ψ is the fundamental Planck-scale motion field.
  2. g_{μν} emerges as ψ-covariance.
  3. GR is the IR limit of ψ dynamics.
  4. Γ_G is the curvature-exchange scalar derived from ψ.
  5. Dark matter & dark energy are unified.
  6. Singularities are avoided.
  7. Particles, quantum behaviour, and gravity have one origin.
  8. The ψ → g → cosmology hierarchy is now fully established.

